| Biblical Hebrew      | English Gloss           |
|---------------------|-------------------------|
| גָּדוֹל              | big                     |
| קָטָן                | small                   |
| חָזָק                | strong                  |
| רָגוּעַ              | calm/settled            |

---

### Prepositions and Conjunctions

| Biblical Hebrew      | English Gloss           |
|---------------------|-------------------------|
| בְּ                 | in/with                 |
| תַּחַת              | under                   |
| אַחַר, אַחֲרֵי        | after                   |
| עַל                 | on/upon                 |
| אֶל                 | toward                  |
| עִם                 | with                    |

---

### Particles, Grammar, and Pronouns

| Biblical Hebrew      | English Gloss                      |
|---------------------|------------------------------------|
| אֶת                 | direct object marker                |
| וַי-, וְ-            | and/then (narrative waw)           |
| הִנֵּה               | behold/see!                        |
| כֻּלָּם              | all of them/everyone               |

---

## Grammar

- Sequential actions using וַי- prefix ("and then...") in Qal perfect/imperfect
- Introduction and practice of direct object marker אֶת with definite objects ("to save *Evan*")
- Simple use and repetition of big/small adjectives
- Use of prepositions (בְּ, תַּחַת, עַל, אֶל, עִם, אַחֲרֵי)
- Linking narrative actions with אחרי כן/ואחרי ("after that"/"then")
- Further practice with noun-adjective agreement and simple presentative הנה
- Chaining of actions: "X did…and then Y did…and then…"
- Minimal use of new verbs—primary focus on familiar vocabulary with new contexts (storm/weather/household items)
- Continued use of plural verbs and subjects
- Repetition and illustration of opposites (big/small, storm/calm, laugh/worry)
- Active practice with narrative sequencing within household/adventure context
